Run in test mode
- read in the text file input
- parse the text file input and get the PID-memory usage pairs
- identify the PIDs that exceed the memory limit
- if the dry-run flag is set: output the kill command that will be run to terminate the bloated workers, but do not run the command

Run in live mode
- read in the output from running passenger-memory-stats
- if the dryrun flag is set: output the kill command that will be run to terminate the bloated workers, but do not run the command

